<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="1218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1218">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/8–2145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-19T16:00:00-05:00">October
                                    19, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1017. ReEmb 385, March 21, 1945. Turkish-Soviet Treaty of December 17,
                            1925 and its protocols will expire November 7, 1945. Estimate of
                            probable effect of expiration on Turkish-Soviet relations would be
                            useful.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Ankara as Department’s 1017, repeated to Moscow as Department’s
                            2188, and to London as Department’s 9254.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>